title: Super Mario Bros. Wonder Review
author: @HombreDufff
comment:
The game its a solid 7

+ Game feels fresh: wonder effect, badges and new power ups
+ Character and enemies animation brings new life to the game
+ Visuals
+ N¬∞ of stages + Hub World
+ Memorable stages
+ Characters roster

- Most challenges felt short in duration and lazy
- Some ideas or concepts felt unexploited or way too conservative
- Bosses: lack of variety
- Most badges are useless or "one timers". Most of them had no need to use them more than once or twice.
- Way to many wonder seeds given away/bought
- Standies as collectables were pretty lame
- Game is way too easy compared to Super Mario World/Mario Bros 3
- OST isnt that stimulating besides some few stages
- Multiplayer with no friendly fire ü§¶‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è

Giving Mario Wonder a 9 its way too generous.
